HEADWORD: Neb
<hw>Neb</hw> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>nebb</ets>
head, face; akin to D. <ets>neb</ets>, Icel. <ets>nef</ets>, beak of a
bird, nose, Dan. <ets>naeb</ets> beak, bill, Sw. <ets>n⟦aum⟧bb</ets>,
<ets>n⟦aum⟧f</ets>, and prob. also to D. <ets>sneb</ets>,
<ets>snavel</ets>, bill, beak, G. <ets>schnabel</ets>, Dan. & Sw.
<ets>snabel</ets>, and E. <ets>snap</ets>. Cf. <er>Nib</er>,
<er>Snap</er>, <er>Snaffle</er>.]</ety> <def>The nose; the snout; the
mouth; the beak of a bird; a nib, as of a pen.</def> <altsp>[Also
written <asp>nib</asp>.]</altsp> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

